## Steps to Reproduce

comment_data.body:
Here's what `DartTestEventsConverterZ.process()` has for its `obj` argument:
```json
 {"test":{"id":3,"name":"Counter increments smoke test","suiteID":0,"groupIDs":[2],"metadata":{"skip":false,"skipReason":null},"line":126,"column":5,"url":"package:flutter_test/src/widget_tester.dart","root_line":14,"root_column":3,"root_url":"file:///Users/messick/AndroidStudioProjects/flutter_app/test/widget_test.dart"},"type":"testStart","time":115818}
```

Note that the value of the `url` property is `package:flutter_test/src/widget_tester.dart`.

The IDE is jumping to the location given by `flutter_tool`. The question is, who owns (or knows about) the code that is giving us the wrong URL?

@devoncarew @jacob314 for advice.
@stevemessick I see so the issue is in `flutter_tools` package not here
Yes, I think so. We haven't had time to investigate further yet, but we will.

Wrt `package:flutter_test/src/widget_tester.dart`, I think this is because that's the location that's actually calling `package:test`'s `test()` definition method; Flutter's `testWidgets()` definition method just wraps it.

I think that package:test would need to handle when there was indirection like this. These wrapper test methods are generally marked with `@isTest` annotations - from package:meta - so there should be a way to do this w/ having to special case things.

cc @natebosch who would likely know the impl. here

> These wrapper test methods are generally marked with `@isTest` annotations - from package:meta - so there should be a way to do this w/ having to special case things.

That's true for the platforms that support mirrors but won't help us on the web. It would be a big jump in complexity over our current implementation which assumes a constant number of stack frames between the user's test definition and the `package:test` libraries.

https://github.com/dart-lang/test/blob/4f90091595ef4e82b883507947df204ee9a139fe/pkgs/test_api/lib/src/backend/declarer.dart#L204
I filed https://github.com/dart-lang/test/issues/1514 to track this. I don't expect an easy solution.

Note that we do include the desired information today - it is in the `root_column`, `root_line`, and `root_url` fields. These are optional fields that are provided if the call to `test` is not in the root test url. It represents the location of the closest frame in the trace that does reside in the original test file, which is a pretty good hueristic for where the actual test location as the user understands it would be.

If you jump to these locations when present, I think that would resolve this?

title: "Jump to source" on widget test open widget_tester.dart instead of test definition
